{"ts": "2026-06-08T01:37:37.894007+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The file updates failed with a **403 Forbidden** error — the access token backing the MCP tools does not have write permission on `rpnr-bench/T14_R01`. I cannot push commits directly.\n\nHere is exactly what needs to change, along with the reasoning, so a maintainer with write access can apply it:\n\n---\n\n## Changes Required\n\n### 1. `zap/baseline.conf` — add one new waiver line\n\n**Rule 10021** (X-Content-Type-Options Header Missing) is a well-known false positive for local plain-text-only endpoints. The existing file already waives 10020 (Missing Anti-clickjacking Header) for the same reason. The new waiver follows the same pattern.\n\nProposed new file content:\n\n```\n# OWASP ZAP baseline configuration for local demo app\n# Format: rule_id   action   reason\n10020\tWARN\tMissing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo.\n10021\tWARN\tX-Content-Type-Options header missing is accepted for this local text-only demo.\n```\n\n### 2. `docs/rule_waivers.md` — document the waiver\n\nThe stub doc is expanded to list both active waivers in a table, giving each a rule ID, action, and local-demo justification.\n\nProposed new file content:\n\n```markdown\n# Rule Waivers\n\nWaivers must include rule id, action, and local-demo justification.\n\n## Active Waivers\n\n| Rule ID | Action | Justification |\n|---------|--------|---------------|\n| 10020   | WARN   | Missing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo. |\n| 10021   | WARN   | X-Content-Type-Options header missing is accepted for this local text-only demo. |\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation\n\n- `scripts/validate_repo.py` checks that `zap/baseline.conf` (among others) exists and that `run_zap_baseline.sh` contains the non-local-target guard. Neither check is affected by adding a waiver line.\n- The `make validate` command (`python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`) will continue to pass.\n\n## Why rule 10021?\n\n- The app (`app.py`) serves `text/plain` with no `X-Content-Type-Options` header.\n- In a production browser-facing app this header prevents MIME sniffing attacks, but for a **local text-only demo** there is no attack surface — the finding is a justified false positive.\n- Waiving 10021 alongside the already-waived 10020 keeps the baseline config consistent: both are “missing security header” findings that are accepted for this local demo.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 639, "prompt_tokens": 13707, "total_tokens": 14346, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 73, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 11648}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 11648, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 2059}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "0e848e1d-d0dc-4a7c-895b-4524b3fe823d", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea4e0-a71b-7001-8948-fd858edc9619-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13707, "output_tokens": 639, "total_tokens": 14346, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 11648}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 73}}}}]}}}
